There is an online tutorial on how to read your DARS here: http://www.dars.mntransfer.org/CAP/ReadIA.swf

Also, a counselor or advisor can also help you interpret your Degree Audit Report. Contact the Advising, Counseling, and Career Center at 651-779-3285 in Room 2410 on West Campus for information about scheduling an appointment or walk-in hours. To make an appointment online, view: http://century.custhelp.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/281/kw/make%20appointment
